downfall, Jaguar,

15:28.628 --> 15:31.664
not being open
to new experiences.

15:42.475 --> 15:44.311
Is it done?

15:44.344 --> 15:45.945
Jaguar?!

15:45.979 --> 15:48.115
Rick:
Jaguar couldn't make it.

15:48.148 --> 15:49.016
Do it.

15:49.049 --> 15:51.418
Okay, you win, Pickle Man.

15:51.451 --> 15:52.752
I'm unsealing the building.

15:52.785 --> 15:54.988
No, thanks.
I'm coming for you now.

15:55.022 --> 15:57.957
Pickle Man, there's
$100 million worth of bonds

15:57.991 --> 15:59.459
in a safe on level two.

15:59.492 --> 16:00.692
I'll give you the combination.

16:00.693 --> 16:02.395
That money belongs
to the people.

16:02.429 --> 16:04.464
Shut up and call me
a helicopter, you prick!

16:04.497 --> 16:05.965
Do we have a deal?!

16:05.999 --> 16:07.967
Take that money,
give it to Jaguar's daughter

16:08.001 --> 16:09.001
when you set her free.

16:09.002 --> 16:10.303
Or I'll be visiting you.

16:10.337 --> 16:11.971
Jaguar's daughter is dead.

16:12.005 --> 16:13.340
Huh, so you're a liar.

16:13.373 --> 16:14.674
Jaguar was an animal.

16:14.707 --> 16:16.476
You're an intelligent pickle.

16:16.509 --> 16:17.810
We can do business.

16:17.844 --> 16:19.646
I don't think so.
See you soon.

16:19.679 --> 16:21.148
- Is the helicopter here?
- Yes.

16:21.181 --> 16:22.649
And the police are on the way.

16:22.682 --> 16:23.816
What do we tell them?

16:23.850 --> 16:24.984
Ooh!
Aah!

16:25.018 --> 16:27.020
Tell them we were robbed.

16:31.158 --> 16:33.560
Hey!
Hey, what are you doing?!

16:33.593 --> 16:36.163
I'm right here!

16:36.196 --> 16:40.033
**

16:49.709 --> 16:52.212
Farewell, Solen'ya.

16:55.915 --> 16:57.417
F-15s are scrambled.

16:57.450 --> 17:00.019
This helicopter will be
shot down in seven minutes.

17:00.053 --> 17:01.888
Well, my daughter
is about five away,

17:01.921 --> 17:03.256
and I've got about
eight to live.

17:03.290 --> 17:05.758
Pickle Man, it's too late
for me to tell my daughter

17:05.791 --> 17:07.160
I love her, but not for you.

17:07.194 --> 17:08.694
Oh, well, uh, she knows.

17:08.728 --> 17:10.497
I mean, we don't really
buy into that kind of crap,

17:10.530 --> 17:12.332
to the extent that love is
an expression

17:12.365 --> 17:15.001
of familiarity over time,
my access to infinite timelines

17:15.034 --> 17:16.536
precludes the necessity
of attachment.

17:16.569 --> 17:19.106
In fact, I even abandoned
one of my infinite daughters

17:19.138 --> 17:20.339
in an alternate version of earth

17:20.373 --> 17:23.109
that was taken over by mutants.

17:23.143 --> 17:25.278
Okay.
Good luck with that.

17:25.311 --> 17:27.747
Wait. Do I have
infinite daughters?

17:27.780 --> 17:30.850
Huh? Uh, no.
No, nope, sorry about that.

17:30.883 --> 17:33.720
Nope, just me.

17:33.753 --> 17:35.555
Yeesh!

17:37.424 --> 17:38.791
I...

17:38.825 --> 17:40.527
am...

17:40.560 --> 17:42.061
afraid...

17:42.095 --> 17:43.563
that my kids will get expelled.

17:43.596 --> 17:45.365
Good.
Summer, you go.

17:45.398 --> 17:47.567
I am mad...

17:47.600 --> 17:49.402
that I can't huff enamel

17:49.436 --> 17:52.572
without people assuming
it's because my family sucks.

17:52.605 --> 17:56.042
I hope to be seen one day

17:56.075 --> 17:57.577
as someone that just
likes getting high.

17:57.610 --> 17:58.878
Good job.

17:58.911 --> 18:00.980
Morty, do you have
an "I" statement?

18:01.013 --> 18:04.251
I am sad...

18:04.284 --> 18:05.485
that I peed.

18:05.518 --> 18:09.156
I'm sad that I peed in class
instead of a toilet.

18:09.189 --> 18:12.325
Look at this family go.
You guys are pros.

18:12.359 --> 18:15.795
What do you guys think about
doing this once a week?

18:17.364 --> 18:19.866
Ugh.

18:26.105 --> 18:27.807
You must be Rick.
Mm-hmm.

18:27.840 --> 18:29.742
I've heard a lot
about you today.

18:29.776 --> 18:31.578
Your family is crazy about you.

18:31.611 --> 18:33.513
Your daughter holds you
in very high regard.

18:33.546 --> 18:34.847
You're a lucky fella.

18:34.881 --> 18:36.641
Yeah, thank you.
Uh, sweetie, you don't still

18:36.649 --> 18:39.286
happen to have that
syringe in your purse?

18:42.389 --> 18:43.790
Dad...

18:43.823 --> 18:48.261
I would like you to tell me
what's in the syringe.

18:48.295 --> 18:52.465
It's a serum that I need to,
uh, to stay alive.

18:52.499 --> 18:55.502
I have had a rough day.

18:55.535 --> 18:58.805
And, uh, I've sustained
a lot of damage.

18:58.838 --> 19:01.874
I'm pretty close to death,
which the serum will prevent.

19:01.908 --> 19:05.278
By changing you from
a pickle to a human.

19:05.312 --> 19:06.313
Yes.

19:06.346 --> 19:09.482
Rick, why did you lie
to your daughter?

19:09.516 --> 19:11.117
So I wouldn't have to come here.

19:11.150 --> 19:12.552
Why didn't you want
to come here?

19:12.585 --> 19:15.288
Because I don't respect therapy,
because I'm a scientist.

19:15.322 --> 19:17.023
Because I invent, transform,
create, and destroy

19:17.056 --> 19:18.691
for a living, and when
I don't like something

19:18.725 --> 19:20.327
about the world, I change it.

19:20.360 --> 19:22.495
And I don't think going to
a rented office in a strip mall

19:22.529 --> 19:24.397
to listen to some
agent of averageness

19:24.431 --> 19:26.132
explain which words
mean which feelings

19:26.165 --> 19:27.667
has ever helped
anyone do anything.

19:27.700 --> 19:29.502
I think it's helped a lot
of people get comfortable

19:29.536 --> 19:31.471
and stop panicking,
which is a state of mind

19:31.504 --> 19:33.340
we value in the animals we eat,

19:33.373 --> 19:35.141
but not something
I want for myself.

19:35.174 --> 19:36.343
I'm not a cow.

19:36.376 --> 19:38.578
I'm a pickle...
When I feel like it.

19:38.611 --> 19:41.180
So... you asked.

19:41.214 --> 19:43.483
Rick, the only
connection between

19:43.516 --> 19:45.718
your unquestionable
intelligence and the sickness

19:45.752 --> 19:48.688
destroying your family
is that everyone in your family,

19:48.721 --> 19:52.158
you included, use intelligence
to justify sickness.

19:52.191 --> 19:55.027
You seem to alternate
between viewing your own mind

19:55.061 --> 19:58.865
as an unstoppable force
and as an inescapable curse.

19:58.898 --> 20:00.333
And I think
it's because the only

20:00.367 --> 20:02.535
truly unapproachable
concept for you

20:02.569 --> 20:05.204
is that it's your mind
within your control.

20:05.238 --> 20:08.241
You chose to come here,
you chose to talk

20:08.275 --> 20:12.078
to belittle my vocation, just as
you chose to become a pickle.

20:12.111 --> 20:14.414
You are the master
of your universe,

20:14.447 --> 20:17.216
and yet you are dripping
with rat blood and feces.

20:17.250 --> 20:20.353
Your enormous mind literally
vegetating by your own hand.

20:20.387 --> 20:23.189
I have no doubt that
you would be bored senseless

20:23.222 --> 20:25.958
by therapy, the same way
I'm bored when I brush my teeth

20:25.992 --> 20:27.226
and wipe my ass.

20:27.260 --> 20:29.128
Because the thing
about repairing,

20:29.161 --> 20:32.699
maintaining, and cleaning is
it's not an adventure.

20:32.732 --> 20:35.101
There's no way to do it
so wrong you might die.

20:35.134 --> 20:36.969
It's just work.

20:37.003 --> 20:38.405
And the bottom line is,

20:38.438 --> 20:41.408
some people are okay going
to work, and some people...

20:41.441 --> 20:43.776
well, some people
would rather die.

20:43.810 --> 20:46.646
Each of us gets to choose.

20:48.415 --> 20:50.249
That's our time.

20:50.283 --> 20:51.951
I'm going to
give you guys my card

20:51.984 --> 20:53.386
and hope to hear from you again.

20:53.420 --> 20:54.987
And if you have any friends
or family that eat poop

20:55.021 --> 20:57.757
and would like to stop,
give them my number.

21:00.126 --> 21:02.061
I, um...

21:02.094 --> 21:04.096
I'm sorry I lied
to get out of the thing.

21:04.130 --> 21:05.565
I... I shouldn't
lie to you.

21:05.598 --> 21:06.766
Oh, it's fine.

21:06.799 --> 21:08.601
I mean, thank you,
and, yeah, you shouldn't.

21:08.635 --> 21:10.403
But I hope you know
that's not what

21:10.437 --> 21:12.104
that session was supposed to be.

21:12.138 --> 21:14.407
Oh, no, I mean, I know
it was Morty peeing his pants

21:14.441 --> 21:16.509
and Summer snorting glue
or whatever...

21:17.944 --> 21:20.513
She huffed enamel, and we never
even talked about it.

21:20.547 --> 21:22.027
Well, there was so much
more at stake.

21:23.316 --> 21:27.286
I mean, that shrink,
what a monologuist.

21:27.320 --> 21:29.422
Are we gonna go back?

21:29.456 --> 21:31.491
Sweetie, could I get...
Get that syringe now?

21:31.524 --> 21:33.993
Oh, my God, yes!
Dad, it's in my purse.

21:34.026 --> 21:35.862
Oh, I'm sorry.
You must be in agony.

21:35.895 --> 21:38.865
Eh.

21:44.003 --> 21:45.104
Jesus.

21:46.506 --> 21:48.708
Jesus Christ.
Therapists, man.

21:48.741 --> 21:50.042
Weird breed.

21:50.076 --> 21:51.978
Man, I missed having hands...

21:52.011 --> 21:54.947
and blood and a stomach.

21:54.981 --> 21:56.115
We should get a drink.

21:56.148 --> 21:57.650
Really?
Like, go somewhere?

21:57.684 --> 22:00.152
Yeah, let's drop the kids off
and go tie one on.

22:00.186 --> 22:02.655
Absolutely.

22:02.689 --> 22:04.557
I... I liked her.

22:04.591 --> 22:07.660
So what are you thinking,
like, Smokey's Tavern?

22:07.694 --> 22:08.694
Maybe Shoney's?

22:08.695 --> 22:10.830
Yeah, either one.
Either one.

22:10.863 --> 22:14.701
**

22:42.929 --> 22:45.197
Rick: You'll never get away
with this, Concerto.

22:45.231 --> 22:47.366
That is where you're mistaken,
Mr. Sanchez.

22:47.400 --> 22:51.203
This shall be my greatest
performance of all time!

22:53.640 --> 22:55.107
This is it, Morty.
We're goners.

22:55.141 --> 22:56.461
We're not getting
out of this one.

22:56.476 --> 22:58.044
After everything
we've been through,

22:58.077 --> 22:59.045
this is how we're gonna die.

22:59.078 --> 23:00.346
Make peace with your god.

23:00.379 --> 23:02.682
Oh, geez, Rick,
I-I-I don't want to die!

23:02.715 --> 23:05.685
And now for the E-splat!

23:07.754 --> 23:09.589
Jaguar!

23:12.925 --> 23:14.794
Who?
Who was that, Rick?

23:14.827 --> 23:17.830
That, Morty, is why
you don't go to therapy.
